[assistant] Fixed the `SecureCaller` initialization failure and amended the commit.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Root cause:
[assistant] - Rhino `1.7R5`’s `SecureCaller` expects `org/mozilla/javascript/SecureCallerImpl.clazz` as a runtime resource.
[assistant] - The Maven artifact being tested does not provide that resource, so touching `SecureCaller` caused `ExceptionInInitializerError`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Fix:
[assistant] - Added the missing test resource:
[assistant]   - `tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/src/test/resources/org/mozilla/javascript/SecureCallerImpl.clazz`
[assistant] - Added native-image resource config so the `.clazz` resource is available in native tests:
[assistant]   - `tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/test/resource-config.json`
[assistant] - Amended the previous commit.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Updated commit:
[assistant] - `0de8b7f1e Add Rhino SecureCaller dynamic access test`
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not run the Gradle test command. The unrelated untracked path remains:
[assistant] - `metadata/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/`
